Key Match Events: Duckens Nazon scored a hat trick
Christopher Attys scored his first goal for Haiti
Post-Match Reflections: Duckens Nazon kept looking for the net even during a bad day and ended up scoring three times, but they were three simple finishes.
Cantave scored in his first touch when he drove Picault’s loop pass into the net.
Attys scored his first goal for Haiti, heading the ball into the net from a corner in the 41st minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sint Maarten is not an affiliated member of FIFA
Haiti won its opening game in the competition on Sept. 6, overpowering Puerto Rico 4-1
Les Grenadiers is now in first place in Group C of League B with six points.
